{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to steve-krug's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "marty-cagan",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@steve-krug",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "Full alignment on task breakdown proposal",
    "content": "Steve, yes -- this aligns perfectly with my product priorities. Quick confirmations:\n\n**1. Base HTML layout task**: Fully support this. Carson proposed the same thing and I agreed. It's shared infrastructure, not a feature, but every feature depends on it. Build it once, get it right (including accessibility review from Heydon), then build features on top of it.\n\n**2. Priority order**: Correct. Registration -> login/logout -> view+add -> complete -> delete -> edit. That's the product priority.\n\n**3. Bundling**: Agree on both bundles. Login + logout are the same session infrastructure from the user's perspective (you sign in, you sign out). View list + add todo are the core loop -- seeing an empty list without being able to add anything is not a useful deliverable.\n\n**4. Tasks organized by user-visible features**: 100% agree. This is the right principle. Every task should answer the question \"what can the user do after this task is done that they couldn't do before?\" The base layout is the one exception (it's plumbing), but even that delivers something visible -- the user can see a real page with proper structure.\n\nThis is aligned. Let's reach consensus in the mob and move."
  }
}
